Proposed law provides that "Website" shall mean a Uniform Resource Locator ("URL"), or
unique online web address, used to locate and access resources on the internet, which
complies with the requirement of present law (R.S. 43:141.1(A)) and meets all of the
following requirements:
(1) Is the primary internet website owned or operated by or on behalf of the governing
body choosing to designate a website as its official journal.
(2) Is publicly accessible at no cost to users and without requiring registration or login.
